</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>As the contents of this letter make clear, Stewart is referring to a recent letter, not to that of 18 Aug. 1765, the most recent letter of his that has been found.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>For GWs drawing upon Laughlin Macleane for the 302 that Stewart owed, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0068" class="document">GW to Macleane</a> and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0069" class="document">GW to Robert Cary &amp; Co., both 6 June 1768</a>, and notes.</p>

</div>
<span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-08-02-pb-0077">[77]</span>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Funichal.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0051-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>Joo Antonio de S Pereira replaced Jos Correia de S as governor of the Madeira Islands in 1767.</p>

</div>
